# Random-hash .mp3 files (not project artifacts; likely cache from other tools).
/*.mp3
/*.wav
/*.m4a

# --- Claude Code / agent artifacts -------------------------------------------
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/state/
.claude/runs/
.claude/transcripts/

# --- GSD (project planning is committed; runtime artifacts are not) ---------
# NOTE: .planning/state/ is git-tracked per MEM-11 (.planning/state/ = planning state = tracked)
# Only runtime/dynamic session subdirs and temporary files are excluded:
# dynamic per-session subdirs (content is ephemeral; .gitkeep is tracked)
.planning/state/sessions/*/
.planning/runs/

# --- Tarballs / archives -----------------------------------------------------
*.zip
*.tar
*.gz
!Inputs/Principles/*.zip

# --- Node (in case future tooling brings it in) ------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# --- Transient research / HTTP cache (regenerated every run) -----------------
runs/_cache/
runs/research/

# --- Workflow-internal provenance scratch (intermediate args/results) -------
# Underscore-prefixed = engine internals, reproducible; not investor deliverables.
outputs/portfolio/flagship/_provenance/
outputs/portfolio/flagship/_widen_dna/

# --- External handoff package (lives OUTSIDE the repo tree) ------------------
# The investor/operator handoff bundle is built to ../29.Engine-handoff/ and may
# carry live credentials. Belt-and-braces: if it is ever regenerated in-tree,
# it must never be stageable. See scripts/build_handoff_tarball.sh.
handoff_vladimir/
/TELEGRAM_FOR_VLADIMIR.txt
